    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Financial Analysis of Carborundum Universal Madras India Limited (CUMI)</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">V.Kasi Viswanathan</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Financial Analysis of Carborundum Universal<br />Madras India Limited</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2011 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5364</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">FINANCIAL statement is prepared for the purpose of presenting a periodical review
or report by the management and deal with the state of investment in business and result
achieved during the period of under review. Analysis of financial performance includes
breaking financial performance and finding out ratios and percentage. Thus, the above said
all process helps in drawing certain results from the financial performance and its
interpretation include both analysis and criticism.
In this study an attempt has been made to “an analysis on performance of various
business segments of carborundum universal limited” to interept its results by using the
various tools of finance namely.
• Comparative Balance Sheet.
• Ratio analysis
• Cash flow statements analysis
• Schedule of changes in working capital
The methodology followed for the study in case method since the study confined to a
particular unit. The period of study is for five years from 2005-2006 to 2009-2010 and in the
study various accounting tools namely ,ratio analysis and comparative balance sheet analysis.
Major objective of the study is to find out the best business segment of carborundum
universal limited among the three segment (Abrasives, Ceramics, and Electro
minerals),abrasives is considered as the best segment, because% of companies profit is
gained from the manufacturing of abrasives and earner a net profit of 507.23 million during
the year 2010. But electro minerals and ceramics business profit also increasing every year,
so company may concentrate on these business two also. It will give good reputation for
company in the market.</td></tr>
